S

setAlgoType(AlgoType) - Method in class net.equasoft.ratingreminder.RatingReminder
Specify a pre-defined algorithm that will decide to trigger or not the alert dialog each time RatingReminder is executed There are 3 algorithm :
AlgoType.NO_GAP_ALGO this algo returns always true AlgoType.REGULAR_ALGO this algo returns true each time the app started a number of times equals to "gap" AlgoType.DOUBLE_GAP_ALGO this algo returns true each time the app started a number of times equals to "gap", "gap" being multiplied by 2 at each hit
setAppName(String) - Method in class net.equasoft.ratingreminder.fragment.AskingDialogFragment

setDialogType(RatingDialogType) - Method in class net.equasoft.ratingreminder.RatingReminder
Specify a pre-defined dialog type There are 2 dialog types :
RatingDialogType.BASIC_DIALOG define a very simple alert dialog RatingDialogType.IMAGE_DIALOG define an alert dialog decorated with an image

setGap(int) - Method in class net.equasoft.ratingreminder.RatingReminder
This method sets the field "gap" an int value that is used by the chosen algo to trigger a dialog display
This field is useless when the algo AlgoType.NO_GAP_ALGO is selected
